The Trinity did not come to be out of a necessity to say to the world that though they see Jesus
Christ as God, the Father as God, and the Holy Spirit as God, that they still believe in one God
Though this need was considered, after all, the Hebrews worshipped and believed in one God, it
wasn't the case. Rather, the Trinity is plainly and solely scriptural. The very essence or substance
of the Triune God is all three persons. One God, three persons. So when Nicaea came around and
the bishops sought to close the case of Arianism, homoousios was the one word that did, It
effectually solidified the past four years 'worth of teachings of God's essence or or substance by
taking the pre-niceae church's concept of God's unique substance and putting a word to it
Homoousios means "one substance,' or "same substance." Jesus is the same substance as the
Father. The reason substance was a huge deal was because the understanding was that there were
two substances. One of creation: angels, spirits, souls, the earth, and the heaven and one of God
They did not see God to be of the same substance that all of creation comprises. They easily
understood this because God is the creator of all things and is independent of His creation
Nothing or no one created God or Jesus. 'They never came
being. They are the first and the
