So, that means we never came into existence through God's will, whether that be the Father, or
the Son, or the Holy Spirit. We were created, as per LDS doctrine, but we did not come into
existence per Rev 11, which contradicts their nature of the godhead. The very fact ALL THING
came into existence by the will of God means that the creator and creature distinction is
warranted, even if my opponent wants to argue Greek philosophy distorted Christianity, which
he's done time and again.
